## Bundled Third-Party Components

The following upstream codebases are bundled in this repository and remain
subject to their own upstream licenses:

### 1. SAM 3 (`sam3/`)

Licensed under the SAM License.

See `sam3/LICENSE` for the full license text.

Official sources:
- https://github.com/facebookresearch/sam3
- https://huggingface.co/facebook/sam3

The bundled `sam3/` subtree and the corresponding upstream checkpoints are
subject to the SAM License.

### 2. SAM 3D Objects (`sam-3d-objects/`)

Licensed under the SAM License.

See `sam-3d-objects/LICENSE` for the full license text.

Official source:
- https://github.com/facebookresearch/sam-3d-objects

The bundled `sam-3d-objects/` subtree and the corresponding upstream
checkpoints are subject to the SAM License.

### 3. ComfyUI (`comfyui/`)

Licensed under the GNU General Public License, Version 3.

See `comfyui/LICENSE` for the full license text.

Official source:
- https://github.com/comfyanonymous/ComfyUI

### 4. Depth Pro (`ml-depth-pro/`)

Licensed under Apple's LICENSE terms.

See `ml-depth-pro/LICENSE` for the full license text.

Additional third-party notices are provided in
`ml-depth-pro/ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS.md`.

Official source:
- https://github.com/apple/ml-depth-pro

The bundled Depth Pro code and the upstream Depth Pro model weights are both
released under the LICENSE terms referenced above.

### 5. Nerfstudio (`nerfstudio/`)

Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0.

See `nerfstudio/LICENSE` for the full license text.
See also: https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

Official source:
- https://github.com/nerfstudio-project/nerfstudio

## External Model Weights Referenced By Workflows Or Setup

This repository ships ComfyUI workflow definitions and setup instructions that
reference or download additional model weights. Those weights are not bundled
in this repository unless a user downloads them separately. Their upstream
licenses apply independently.

### 6. FLUX.2 [klein] 9B / 9B Base model family

The shipped workflows under `comfyui/scenes_workflows/` reference FLUX.2
[klein] 9B model files such as:
- `flux-2-klein-base-9b-fp8.safetensors`
- `flux-2-klein-9b-fp8.safetensors`

The upstream FLUX.2 [klein] 9B family is published under a FLUX
Non-Commercial license on its Hugging Face model pages.

Official sources:
- https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.2-klein-9b-fp8
- https://huggingface.co/black-forest-labs/FLUX.2-klein-base-9b-fp8

IMPORTANT: Using the FLUX.2 [klein] 9B family is restricted by the upstream
non-commercial terms.

### 7. Qwen model families and Qwen-derived artifacts

The shipped workflows under `comfyui/scenes_workflows/` reference Qwen-based
model files such as:
- `qwen_image_edit_2509_fp8_e4m3fn.safetensors`
- `Qwen-Image-Edit-2509-Lightning-4steps-V1.0-bf16.safetensors`
- `qwen_2.5_vl_7b_fp8_scaled.safetensors`
- `qwen_3_8b_fp8mixed.safetensors`

Official Qwen model families referenced by those local filenames include:
- Qwen-Image-Edit
- Qwen2.5-VL
- Qwen3

The corresponding upstream model pages state Apache License 2.0:
- https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen-Image-Edit-2509
- https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen2.5-VL-7B-Instruct
- https://huggingface.co/Qwen/Qwen3-8B
- https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0

This repository also references `lightx2v/Qwen-Image-Lightning`, whose model
page states Apache License 2.0:
- https://huggingface.co/lightx2v/Qwen-Image-Lightning

Some local workflow filenames are ComfyUI-oriented repackagings,
quantizations, or format conversions of upstream Qwen model families. If you
download a repackaged artifact, check both the original model-family license
and the page from which the packaged artifact is obtained.

### 8. FLUX support artifacts used by current setup instructions

The current `setup.sh` downloads the following files when they are missing:
- `flux2-vae.safetensors`
- `qwen_3_8b_fp8mixed.safetensors`

The current setup source for those files is:
- https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/vae-text-encorder-for-flux-klein-9b

Those support artifacts are not bundled in this repository. They are obtained
separately, may be packaging-specific, and should be checked against the
upstream source page actually used at download time together with the
underlying model-family terms.

## Source-Installed Setup-Time Dependencies

The setup process also installs some third-party code directly from upstream
GitHub repositories. Those source trees are not bundled here merely by being
installed during setup, but their upstream licenses still apply to use,
redistribution, and packaging of those installed components.

### 9. GitHub source installs used by setup

Current examples from `setup.sh` include:

- `NVlabs/nvdiffrast`, published under a BSD-style license in its upstream
  `LICENSE.txt`
  - https://github.com/NVlabs/nvdiffrast
- `NVlabs/tiny-cuda-nn`, published under a BSD-style license in its upstream
  `LICENSE.txt`
  - https://github.com/NVlabs/tiny-cuda-nn
- `autonomousvision/mip-splatting`, whose upstream repository is published
  under the Gaussian-Splatting License with research and non-commercial
  restrictions
  - https://github.com/autonomousvision/mip-splatting

The setup script uses the `mip-splatting` source tree as the installation
source for `diff-gaussian-rasterization`. If you package or redistribute that
installed code, review the exact upstream source tree and license files that
were used.

### 10. Direct Git dependencies exposed through bundled subprojects

The bundled `sam-3d-objects/` dependency files also reference additional
upstream Git-based dependencies, including:

- `nerfstudio-project/gsplat`, Apache License 2.0
  - https://github.com/nerfstudio-project/gsplat
- `facebookresearch/pytorch3d`, BSD License
  - https://github.com/facebookresearch/pytorch3d
- `microsoft/MoGe`, MIT License, with Apache 2.0-licensed DINOv2 code inside
  the upstream MoGe repository
  - https://github.com/microsoft/MoGe

These are not bundled in the repository root merely by being declared in
dependency files, but their upstream terms still apply if they are installed,
packaged, or redistributed.

## Usage Notes

1. The original WorldMesh code is MIT-licensed, but each third-party component
   listed above remains subject to its own license.

2. If you download or use external model weights or setup-time source
   dependencies referenced by this repository, you must comply with their
   upstream terms even when those files are not bundled in this repository.

3. If you redistribute the bundled `comfyui/` subtree or derivative works of
   it, you must comply with the GNU GPL v3 terms applicable to that component.

4. The SAM License applies to the bundled `sam3/` and `sam-3d-objects/`
   components and to the corresponding upstream checkpoints. Among other terms,
   it requires acknowledgement of SAM materials in research publications.

5. Depth Pro includes additional upstream acknowledgements in
   `ml-depth-pro/ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS.md`.

6. This summary is not exhaustive for every transitive pip, conda, or system
   dependency used during development or runtime.

7. If a third-party license or notice was missed in this summary, that omission
   does not remove the upstream licensor's rights or your compliance
   obligations. The practical remediation is typically to identify the omitted
   component, add the missing notice or attribution, and if necessary stop
   redistributing the affected bundle until the licensing position is corrected.

8. This file is intended as a practical summary for the public source
   repository. Commercial deployment, packaged redistribution, container
   distribution, or bundling of downloaded checkpoints should be reviewed
   separately against the exact upstream artifacts used.

9. For complete terms, consult the linked upstream license files, model pages,
   and local vendored license files.
